Laurence Paynter

Laurence Paynter is a freelance Web Developer, who originally studied Fine Art at Saint Martins, then switched to Biomedical Sciences & Nutrition, then to IT, then Herbal Medicine and back to IT again

Apart from his passion for technology, human health and art, Laurence loves playing, studying and teaching chess

After a number of years playing for Clifton Chess Club in the Bristol Chess League and in various tournaments,  Laurence taught chess in some of Bristol's primary schools; helping children to move away from their screens and become excited about learning to play the best game ever devised 

Laurence also brought chess to Chandos House, to help troubled men struggling with addiction 

Chess has been shown to have numerous benefits for cognitive function, improving memory, concentration and self-esteem; alongside many other benefits it is great fun